<item>
            <title>[PIG-2162] bin/pig should not modify user args</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2162</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>
&lt;p&gt;PIG launcher script (bin/pig) joins all the user arguments in one string. This leads to confusion when the arguments contain spaces.&lt;br/&gt;
i.e. &apos;&lt;tt&gt;bin/pig -p sub=&quot;i &amp;gt; 2&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;&apos; is should not same as &apos;&lt;tt&gt;bin/pig -p &quot;sub&quot; &quot;i&quot; &quot;&amp;gt;&quot; &quot;2&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;&apos;, but it is.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
